# hilavitkutin, Architecture Design

> Morsel-driven pipeline execution engine. `#![no_std]`, no alloc.
> Consumers declare WorkUnits with typed read/write access sets; the
> engine analyses them into phases/trunks/fibers, compiles per-core
> dispatch programs, runs them on a pre-allocated thread pool.

The authoritative source is `design_rounds/202603181200_topic.hilavitkutin-design-consolidation.md` (22 domains, 9 cross-domain resolutions, 2480 lines). This doc is a map into that spec.

## Crate layout

| Crate | Role |
|-------|------|
| `hilavitkutin-api` | Consumer-facing types + traits + platform contracts. WorkUnit, AccessSet, Column/Resource/Virtual, Context, Contains, Clock/MemoryProvider/ThreadPool. Consumer contract surface (capability / sink / codec) for API positions that receive or emit items outside WU execution. |
| `hilavitkutin` | Engine: plan, dispatch, resource, thread, strategy, adapt, scheduler. |
| `hilavitkutin-build` | Build-time optimisations (LLVM passes, MIR, cfg emission, PGO/BOLT workflows). Standalone build-dep, no runtime deps. |
| `hilavitkutin-ctx` | Provider-gated context framework (ecosystem, standalone). |
| `hilavitkutin-extensions` | Contract-bound extension host orchestration (descriptor, lifecycle, capability dispatch, failure policy) layered over `hilavitkutin-linking`. Domain-agnostic. `no_std`, no allocator, no dyn. |
| `hilavitkutin-extensions-macros` | Proc-macro companion to `hilavitkutin-extensions`. Emits `#[repr(C)]` descriptor + exported-symbol fn + capability trampolines via `#[export_extension]`. Only proc-macro crate in the stack. |
| `hilavitkutin-kit` | Kit preset trait. Declarative bundle: `type Units` (cons-list of WorkUnits) plus `type Owned` (cons-list of Resources / Columns / Virtuals). Engine reads associated types at compile time on `.add_kit::<K>()`. Standalone (no other hilavitkutin-crate deps). |
| `hilavitkutin-linking` | Cross-platform dynamic library loading primitive (dlopen / LoadLibrary + typed Symbol / StaticRef). Pull-based explicit-symbol resolution. `no_std`, no allocator. Renamed from prior `hilavitkutin-extensions` in round 202604240615. |
| `hilavitkutin-persistence` | Generic hot-cold storage bridge (ecosystem, standalone). |
| `hilavitkutin-providers` | Default Resource-backed providers for the scheduler. v0 ships the interner value-type surface (InternerApi / HasInterner / MemoryArena + default_interner constructor) plus the declarative `InternerKit` (round-4 shape: `type Units = read![]`, `type Owned = read![Resource<...>]`). Future modules add ColumnStorage / Clock / Memory defaults per consumer demand. Standalone (no engine dep). |
| `hilavitkutin-str` | Interned string system (ecosystem, standalone). |

## Dependency graph

A consumer crate depends on `hilavitkutin`. The engine pulls `hilavitkutin-api` plus the arvo crates it needs at runtime: `arvo`, `arvo-bitmask`, `arvo-graph`, `arvo-sparse`, `arvo-spectral` (which itself depends on `arvo-sparse`), and `arvo-comb` (which depends on `arvo-bitmask`). A consumer's `build.rs` separately depends on `hilavitkutin-build`, which has no runtime deps.

hilavitkutin-ctx, -persistence, -str, -kit, -providers are standalone ecosystem crates that consumers opt into. ctx, persistence, str are pure ecosystem (engine does not depend on them). kit is a contract crate the engine depends on for its `.add_kit()` method, but it has no reverse dependency on the engine; consumers can author Kits without pulling the engine in. providers ships default Kit impls consumers wire in (interner, future ColumnStorage / Clock / Memory defaults); it consumes api + str + kit + the foundations crates, no reverse dep.

hilavitkutin-linking, hilavitkutin-extensions, hilavitkutin-extensions-macros make up the plugin-host layer. Downstream consumer ecosystems build domain-specific contract crates on top.

## Vocabulary

Authoritative hierarchy (coarsest → finest):

```
pipeline → core → phase ↔ waist → trunk → fiber ↔ branch ↔ bridge → morsel → micro-morsel → record
```

Dead terms (do not use): chain → fiber, chain group → trunk, partition → phase, archetype → fiber, entity → record, row → record, entry → record, order (on WU) → scheduling hints. See consolidation topic §Vocabulary for full table + rationale.

## Domain map (22 domains across the engine)

| Module | Domains | What it does |
|---|---|---|
| plan::phase | 11 | Waist detection, trunk/branch/bridge assignment |
| plan::fiber | 14 | Fiber formation, whole-fiber feasibility, co-located arena |
| plan::analysis | 15 | Access matrix, RCM, block diagonal, spectral, DP |
| plan::morsel | 12 | Write-only morsel sizing, 3D morsel cube, change detection |
| plan::loading | 16 | Loader WU handling, plan recomputation triggers |
| dispatch | 17 | Monomorphised tuple dispatch, rust-pipe flattener |
| resource | 19 | Stack-local caching, pointer separation |
| thread | 20 | Pre-allocated pool, hybrid wake, core pinning, head+tail |
| strategy | 21 | Plan-time selection, per-phase config, schedule reuse |
| adapt | 22 | Volumetric analysis, EMA metrics, morsel temperature |
| scheduler | 23 | Builder API, self-hosting meta pipeline, version stamps |
| intrinsics | 13 | Day-one asm microkernels, LLVM vectorisation contract |
| platform | 02 | os tier (mmap, pthread, clock_gettime), std tier |

Per-module design lives in `crates/hilavitkutin/DESIGN.md.tmpl`.

## Principles (see PRINCIPLES.md.tmpl)

1. `#![no_std]`, no alloc, every crate.
2. Monomorphisation is the dispatch (no dyn, no TypeId).
3. Pre-allocated thread pool; no runtime spawn beyond plan-time.
4. Schedule once, reuse across frames. Plan recompute is rare.
5. Self-hosting meta pipeline. The scheduler schedules itself.

## Status

**Design mature, zero implementation.** Consolidation topic is complete as of 2026-03-18; latest changelist (03-24) added arvo-bits insertion + strategy markers. Ready to implement bottom-up: hilavitkutin-api first (contracts), then core engine modules.

Design gaps expected during src work:
- Concrete ABI shape of `ExecutionPlan` between phase planner and dispatch emitter.
- Final arvo newtype names for platform trait parameters (ByteCount, Alignment, CoreCount, Nanoseconds).
- Edge cases in strategy selection for unusual DAG shapes.

These land as new `design_rounds/` entries when they surface.

## Consumers

Downstream consumer applications layer on top of hilavitkutin: signal / DAG frameworks, language runtimes (macros, scratch buffers, generative pipelines), and other pipeline-shaped workloads. Each consumer registers its own WorkUnits and storage shapes; the engine schedules them through the same plan / dispatch / adapt loop.
